::main]\r\nasync fn main() {\r\n    let app = Router::new()\r\n        .route(\"/\", connect(handler));\r\n\r\n    let addr = SocketAddr::from(([127, 0, 0, 1], 3000));\r\n    println!(\"listening on {}\", addr);\r\n    axum::Server::bind(&addr)\r\n        .serve(app.into_make_service())\r\n        .await\r\n        .unwrap();\r\n}\r\n\r\nasync fn handler(req: Request<Body>) {\r\n    dbg!(req);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl -v -x \"127.0.0.1:3000\" https://tokio.com/\r\n\r\n*   Trying 127.0.0.1:3000...\r\n* TCP_NODELAY set\r\n* Connected to 127.0.0.1 (127.0.0.1) port 3000 (#0)\r\n* allocate connect buffer!\r\n* Establish HTTP proxy tunnel to tokio.com:443\r\n> CONNECT tokio.com:443 HTTP/1.1\r\n> Host: tokio.com:443\r\n> User-Agent: curl/7.68.0\r\n> Proxy-Connection: Keep-Alive\r\n>\r\n< HTTP/1.1 301 Moved Permanently\r\n< location: tokio.com:443\r\n< content-length: 0\r\n< date: Tue, 26 Oct 2021 08:19:15 GMT\r\n<\r\n* Received HTTP code 301 from proxy after CONNECT\r\n* CONNECT phase completed!\r\n* Closing connection 0\r\ncurl: (56) Received HTTP code 301 from proxy after CONNECT\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf we add a block code after line 778 in routing/mod.rs and add a fallback in `Router`, than we will bypass:\r\n```rust\r\nif path == \"\" {\r\n    if let Some(fallback) = &self.fallback {\r\n        return RouterFuture::from_oneshot(fallback.clone().oneshot(req))\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n```rust\r\n    let app = Router::new()\r\n        .route(\"/\", connect(handler))\r\n        .fallback(handler.into_service());\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe CONNECT request format is valid, we should not use fallback().\r\nIn v0.2.* has a same problem get a 404: https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/discussions/341","closed_by":{"login":"davidpdrsn","id":718941,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcxODk0MQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/718941?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/davidpdrsn","html_url":"https://github.com/davidpdrsn","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/us